comments: Watanabe (BKN) establishes himself in Green's (GSW) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs.
Curry (BKN) moves laterally into Poole's (GSW) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR during his drive toward the rim.
Curry (GSW) briefly rests his hand on Harris' (BKN) side and both players mutually engage and disengage as the pick is being set.
Curry (BKN) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Harris (BKN) moves alongside Curry's (GSW) path and incidental contact occurs as he is guarding Curry's drive toward the rim.
Curry (BKN) reaches in and initiates contact with Looney's (GSW) wrist affecting his shot attempt near the rim.
Thompson (GSW) initiates contact with Irving's (BKN) elbow as he moves into his upward shooting motion.
Irving (BKN) reaches in and initiates contact with Curry's (GSW) right arm during the driving shot attempt.

While contesting the fadeway jump shot, Thompson (GSW) is drawn into the air toward Irving (BKN) and makes marginal contact with Irving (BKN) during his shot attempt. The contact is incidental on his follow through.
Harris (BKN) moves alongside Curry's (GSW) path and maintains a legal guarding position while contesting the shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) and Looney (GSW) mutually engage and disengage in marginal contact as both players position themselves for the rebound.
Looney (GSW) rests his hand on Claxton's (BKN) front and releases away without applying pressure as both players come together on the perimeter.
O'Neale (BKN) extends his leg out and makes intentional foot to ball contact.
Green (GSW) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with O'Neale (BKN) and incidental contact occurs as O'Neale attempts to move over the screen.
Poole (GSW) commits a take foul against Irving (BKN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Harris (BKN) slightly extends his arms into Thompson (GSW), and marginal contact occurs as Thompson moves to set the pick.
Irving (BKN) maintains a verticality and avoids making contact with Poole's (GSW) arm as he is holding the ball on the perimeter.
